{{Infobox lake | name = Storakersvatnet | image = Överuman.jpg | caption = Satellite view of Storakersvatnet (upper left lake) | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Rana, Norway|Rana]], [[Nordland]] | coords = {{Coord|66|10|23|N|14|24|48|E|region:NO_type:waterbody_scale:200000|display=inline,title}} | type = | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = [[Norway]] | length = | width = | area = {{convert|42.30|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = {{convert|78.60|km|abbr=on}} | elevation = {{convert|523|m|abbr=on}} | frozen = | islands = | cities = | reference = [[Norwegian Water Resources and Energy Directorate|NVE]] }}
'''Storakersvatnet''' is a [[lake]] in the municipality of [[Rana, Norway|Rana]] in [[Nordland]] county, [[Norway]]. The lake lies about {{convert|15|km}} south of the town of [[Mo i Rana]] and less than {{convert|900|m}} from the border with [[Sweden]]. The original lake was only {{convert|15.9|km2}}, but a [[dam]] was built at the northern end so that it can serve as a reservoir for the Rana power station. This dam has caused the lake to enlarge to an area of {{convert|42.3|km2}}.<ref name="snl">{{cite web|url=http://snl.no/Store_Akersvatn|title=Store Akersvatn|author=Store norske leksikon|authorlink=Store norske leksikon|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2011-12-15}}</ref>
